  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d91\u0d9a \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0d9a\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0d87\u0dad\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dba\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "An application to find out how many times a vehicle has been oiled in one day",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Police has created an application to know whether one vehicle has taken fuel from different fuel stations in one day while getting fuel for vehicles.",
        "According to Minister of Electricity and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, when the number of a vehicle that has received fuel is entered, it will be shown how the vehicle has received fuel on that date.",
        "He says that this application is currently being tested in various areas of Sri Lanka."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
